## Arachnet Clinical Embeddings — Project Summary

**Owner:** Jan Mura, Arachnet Project z.s.  
**Date started:** March 2026  
**Summary last updated:** 2026-03-26

### What the project is

A clinical terminology embedding platform built on Oracle 23ai in OCI Frankfurt. It ingests SNOMED CT international release RF2 files, builds a structured database, and produces domain-aware vector embeddings combining text, graph/ontology structure, and policy-weighted relationships. The embedding model is custom — not a generic pretrained model — and is parameterised by clinical domain (clinics, health insurance, etc.).

The project uses SNOMED CT under an affiliate licence administered by UZIS (Czech national SNOMED administrator). The product name deliberately avoids the SNOMED trademark. The required SNOMED CT attribution notice is stored in `project.yaml` under `project.snomed_notice` and must appear in all distributed outputs.

