### Key architectural decisions

- Drop/recreate approach for releases (snapshot model, not delta)
- Staging schema pattern: load into snomed_stage, validate, rename-swap to snomed
- Previous production schema retained as snomed_previous after swap (rollback point)
- Inactive SNOMED concepts retained (loaded as-is, not filtered)
- Parquet as intermediate format between RF2 TSV and Oracle load
- OmegaConf for YAML variable interpolation
- oracledb thin client, no Oracle Client installation required
- Passwords in environment variables only, never in YAML or code
- Standard Python venv, not Anaconda
- Phase 0 utilities in src/common/ and scripts/common/
- Two Oracle schemas share one TNS alias, separate credentials
- Separate OCI block volume for data files
- Table load sequence derived from database.yaml order, not a separate list
- No Oracle FK constraints — validation is Python-driven pre-swap SQL checks
- config_schema.md not produced — inline REQUIRED markers are authoritative
- Connection pool is provisional, not used in Phase 1, tune before Phase 4
- National extensions (Czech/Slovak) placeholder in ingestion.yaml, pending UZIS

### Configuration mandatory keys (summary)

Mandatory keys marked with `# REQUIRED` inline in YAML files. Key mandatory ones: `active_environment`, `project.name`, `project.data_release`, `project.snomed_notice`, `environments.<env>.paths.base`, `environments.<env>.paths.log`, `environments.<env>.paths.data_volume`, `environments.<env>.paths.rf2`, `environments.<env>.paths.parquet`, `includes`, `governance.license`, `database.tns_alias`, all schema user and password_env_var fields, `database.tables` (non-empty), all four fields per table entry, `ingestion.release.release_type`, `ingestion.validation.enabled`, `ingestion.swap.strategy`.

### Environment variables required at runtime

`TNS_ADMIN`, `SNOMED_DB_PASSWORD`, `SNOMED_STAGE_DB_PASSWORD`, `SNOMED_ADMIN_DB_PASSWORD` (setup only), `SNOMED_LOG_LEVEL` (optional, default INFO).

